    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nI'm using my cython module in python REPL, find out that class methods that are marked as \"property\" can be executed unexpectedly when I press TAB key to perform auto-completion.\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\r\n# cymod.pyx:\r\ncdef int cnt = 0\r\n\r\ncdef class Bar:\r\n    def __cinit__(self):\r\n        global cnt\r\n        cnt += 1\r\n\r\ncdef class Foo:\r\n    @property\r\n    def bar(self):\r\n        cdef Bar obj = Bar()\r\n        return obj\r\n\r\ndef get_cnt():\r\n    return cnt\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n>>> import cymod\r\n>>> cymod.get_cnt()\r\n0\r\n>>> foo = cymod.Foo()\r\n>>> cymod.get_cnt()\r\n0\r\n>>> bar = foo.bar\r\n>>> cymod.get_cnt()\r\n1\r\n>>> foo.bar\r\n<cymod.Bar object at 0x7f226ebdc7e0>\r\n>>> cymod.get_cnt()\r\n2\r\n>>> foo.bar  <------------------------ press TAB key for several times, then press Ctrl-C\r\nKeyboardInterrupt\r\n>>> cymod.get_cnt()\r\n10  <------------------------ expected to be 2\r\n>>>\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n```python\r\n# pymod.py:\r\ncnt = 0\r\n\r\nclass Bar:\r\n    def __init__(self):\r\n        global cnt\r\n        cnt += 1\r\n\r\nclass Foo:\r\n    @property\r\n    def bar(self):\r\n        obj = Bar()\r\n        return obj\r\n\r\ndef get_cnt():\r\n    return cnt\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n>>> import pymod\r\n>>> pymod.get_cnt()\r\n0\r\n>>> foo = pymod.Foo()\r\n>>> pymod.get_cnt()\r\n0\r\n>>> bar = foo.bar\r\n>>> pymod.get_cnt()\r\n1\r\n>>> foo.bar\r\n<pymod.Bar object at 0x7f226e707390>\r\n>>> pymod.get_cnt()\r\n2\r\n>>> foo.bar  <------------------------ press TAB key for several times, then press Ctrl-C\r\nKeyboardInterrupt\r\n>>> pymod.get_cnt()\r\n2\r\n>>> \r\n```\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.13.0\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.0.11\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
