        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This feels like it's probably a bug in Python 3.13's new repl. Cython properties for cdef classes are just set using the built-in `PyGetSetDef` rather than any special mechanism. Therefore there's really nothing we can do to change this behaviour. \r\n\r\nSo I suggest raising this on the Python issue tracker instead.",
