        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> It would be nice if Cython could at least document this as a known/won't-fix issue.\n\nI'll have a look and see if I can find somewhere good to put it. The difficulty is always trying to find somewhere where it will be read, but where it doesn't scare people who just want to create a property.\n\n> But if not, we'd hope that at least we could get blessing from Cython core devs for the aliasing approach \n\nIf I understand correctly, you're just using the alias to create a normal Python decorator rather than a C one. I'm confident that should keep working.\n\nThe other option I can think of is to do something like\n\n```\n# module scope\nproperty_catches = BaseException if sys.somehow_detect_if_were_in_a_repl else (,)\n\n# In the property\ntry:\n    ...\nexcept property_catches:\n    return None. # ?\n```\n\nObviously one important detail is missing.\n\nThat's potentially something that either you could implement in your wrapper or that Cython could implement (maybe a bit more efficiently than you). It's probably a bit heavy to turn on by default though. I'll investigate at some point\n\n\n",
